He found that the theories he was teaching were not working -- just outside the university walls people lived in squalor.Almost half of Bangladesh 's 112 million people live below the poverty line and about 68 percent of the population are illiterate.The 57-year-old banker knew that poverty was not due to laziness or lack of intelligence but a lack of capital in order to raise cows , make stools or pedal rickshaws.Grameen Bank now has 12,600 staff who visit 36,000 of Bangladesh 's 68,000 villages each week to meet their 2.1 million customers .
